data.enText: to move or make sth move from side to side very quickly and with small movements

data.chText: 每当火车驶过，这些墙都会震动。
data.enText: Every time a train went past the walls vibrated.
The atmosphere seemed to vibrate with tension.

simple_means.memory_skill: vibr 摇摆 + ate 使… → 振动

tr: feel sudden intense sensation or emotion
example: he was thrilled by the speed and the roar of the engine

tr: move or swing from side to side regularly
example: the needle on the meter was oscillating

tr: move back and forth rapidly, usually in an uncontrolled manner

example: The sound resonates well in this theater

tr: waver between conflicting positions or courses of action
example: He oscillates between accepting the new position and retirement

value.def: If something vibrates or if you vibrate it, it shakes with repeated small, quick movements.

example.ex: The ground shook and the cliffs seemed to vibrate...
example.tran: 大地在摇晃，悬崖好像在颤动。

example.ex: The vibrations of the vehicles rattled the shop windows.
example.tran: 车流把商店的窗户震得格格作响。

partsOfSpeech.dec: re 一再 + vibr 摇摆 + ate 做，造成，使… → 一再摇摆 → 再振动
vibr 摇摆 + ant …的，具有…性质的 → 不停摇摆的 → 有活力的
vibr 摇摆 + ancy 状态，性质，状况 → 生机勃勃
vibr 摇摆 + ate 做，造成，使… → 振动
vibr 摇摆 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 振动
vibr 摇摆 + ator 表名词 → 振动装置
